Life coach Solomon Buchi has compared the fan bases of singers Wizkid and Davido. The writer, who is well-known for dropping his two-cent on issues via his social media handles, recently carried out a survey following Wizkid’s loss at the 64th Grammys and his fans’ reactions. Buchi eventually drew up the conclusion that fans of Wizkid known as Wizkid FC are much more violent and problematic compared to Davido’s fans, the 30BG Gang. He advised anyone in a relationship with any Wizkid FC to break up with him or her immediately.   Annie Idibia knocks envious family members     Men who monitor how women spend red flags – Ka3na     Wizkid was nominated in wrong Grammy categories, says Naomi…   “Having observed carefully, I actually think that Wizkid’s fans AKA Wizkid FC are much more violent & problematic than Davido’s fans – 30B Gang. And if your boyfriend/girlfriend is one of them who go around on social media arguing and trolling, dump them right now. Like right now,” Buchi tweeted. After Wizkid’s double loss at the just-concluded Grammys, his fans took to different social media platforms to express their displeasure and grievances. It was reported they stormed the social media pages of the Recording Academy and Angélique Kidjo’s to argue over their fave’s loss